Repeating the regression¶

In [ ]:
using Lathe.preprocess: TrainTestSplit
In [ ]:
test_acc = []
for i in 1:1000
    brca_train, brca_test = TrainTestSplit(brca, 0.75);
    fm = @formula(Patient_Status ~ Protein2 + Protein3 + Protein4 + Modified_Radical_Mastectomy + Lumpectomy);
    logit = glm(fm, brca_train, Binomial(), ProbitLink());
    prediction = GLM.predict(logit,brca_test)
    prediction_class = [if x < 0.5 0 else 1 end for x in prediction];
    correctly_classified = [prediction_class[i] == brca_test.Patient_Status[i] for i in 1:size(brca_test)[1]];
    confmat = MLBase.roc(brca_test.Patient_Status, prediction_class);
    push!(test_acc, (confmat.tp + confmat.tn)/size(brca_test)[1])
end
In [ ]:
boxplot(test_acc, legend = false, size = (500,350), xticks = false, ylim = (0.3,0.8), framestyle = :box,
        title = "Test Accuracy", titlefontsize = 12)
